embeds.title: Getting Support for AdvancedServerList
embeds.description: Please do the following things to receive proper support:

fields.name: Don't ask to ask, just ask!
fields.value: Don't ask in the Chat if it's okay to ask a question, or if someone is around to help you. Simply state your problem/Ask your question directly.

fields.name: Check that the plugin is up-to-date.
fields.value:
Make sure you are using the latest version of the plugin available for your Server version.
You can find downloads on [Modrinth](https://modrinth.com/plugin/advancedserverlist) and [HangarMC](https://hangar.papermc.io/Andre_601/AdvancedServerList) and it supports the latest 1.20 and 1.21 versions (Older versions may be supported, but this is not guaranteed).

fields.name: Explain your issue in detail.
fields.value: Try to provide as much detail as you can. If it helps you explain it better, share screenshots of your problem/your question.

fields.name: Share errors, logs and configuration files.
fields.value:
Make sure to share any errors, log files and Server List configuration files (Files inside `profiles` folder) through a paste site.
https://mclo.gs is recommended for log files, while https://pastes.dev is recommended for configuration files.

fields.name: Check the Wiki
fields.value: Make sure you've checked the [ASL Wiki](https://asl.andre601.ch), as your question/issue may be answered/solved there already.

fields.name: Be Patient
fields.value:
Support is provided on a voluntary basis and without any guarantees. Nobody is obligated to provide you with support and may even choose to refuse it should they choose to.

-# Support is also provided "as is" without any warranty for its correctness.
